My 2 other close friends like to use their phones a lot. They never talk to me often and it always seems weird talking to them. But when they aren #8217;t using their phones they talk to each other. Idk how to explain it. It #8217;s like I don #8217;t have friends, like I #8217;m being rejected. And it #8217;s not like I #8217;m the quiet kid who says nothing at all. I talk to my classmates, like a usual person does. Yet a few or even none I could consider friends. I always sit in class, watching my classmates have fun, talk to each other. Yet here I am alone, sitting there watching them. I always felt a bit envious that they could have such good friends, I want to be like them, where school isn #8217;t such a drag cause they have friends to make it better. I always felt wrong to feel envious of them, like it #8217;s something wrong to think of. But every time, after recess, after school, everyone is talking to their friends, and here am I sitting alone. It feels like no one cares for me. No one remembers my birthday, and yet on any of my classmates birthdays they #8217;d send messages, post on their Instagram Stories, and yet here I am, doing the same to my classmates but no one ever doing it to me. I always thought, why bother, why hassle myself when no one ever cares for me. Because I want friends, I need close friends I could trust. Every time during lessons which has groupwork or it #8217;s PE, no one ever wants me in their group. Heck, I even find the quietest people in my class get a group or have someone to partner up with for PE. I #8217;m always having to ask, and though they accept, it feels like they don #8217;t want me there, like they allowed me in because they didn #8217;t want me to feel sad. But I feel bad, for causing that to others. I #8217;m always the one who walks at the back, the one who goes back home alone.
